      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing, why do i have to keep playing? if the game has no prize and the rules are just designed to make us suffer until we die, why is staying in it considered the \"default\"? it feels less like a choice and more like a sentence. it seems almost more rational to just walk away from the table entirely when you realize the house always wins and the game is rigged for no reason at all.",
